{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":732,"text":"Once upon a time, the world was a big, dysfunctional family."},{"time":5901,"text":"It was run by the great and powerful parents,"},{"time":9332,"text":"and the people were helpless"},{"time":11667,"text":"and hopeless naughty children."},{"time":14163,"text":"If any of the more rowdier children questioned"},{"time":16666,"text":"the authority of the parents, they were scolded."},{"time":20243,"text":"If they went exploring into the parents' rooms,"},{"time":23276,"text":"or even into the secret filing cabinets, they were punished,"},{"time":27059,"text":"and told that for their own good"},{"time":29812,"text":"they must never go in there again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33443,"text":"Then one day, a man came to town"},{"time":35939,"text":"with boxes and boxes of secret documents"},{"time":38737,"text":"stolen from the parents' rooms."},{"time":40601,"text":"\"Look what they've been hiding from you,\" he said."},{"time":44627,"text":"The children looked and were amazed."},{"time":47669,"text":"There were maps and minutes from meetings"},{"time":50513,"text":"where the parents were slagging each other off."},{"time":53778,"text":"They behaved just like the children."},{"time":56326,"text":"And they made mistakes, too, just like the children."},{"time":60284,"text":"The only difference was, their mistakes"},{"time":62995,"text":"were in the secret filing cabinets."},{"time":65820,"text":"Well, there was a girl in the town, and she didn't think"},{"time":68625,"text":"they should be in the secret filing cabinets,"},{"time":71492,"text":"or if they were, there ought to be a law"},{"time":73392,"text":"to allow the children access."},{"time":75509,"text":"And so she set about to make it so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79316,"text":"Well, I'm the girl in that story, and the secret documents"},{"time":83162,"text":"that I was interested in were located in this building,"},{"time":86316,"text":"the British Parliament, and the data that I wanted"},{"time":90678,"text":"to get my hands on were the expense receipts"},{"time":93339,"text":"of members of Parliament."},{"time":97228,"text":"I thought this was a basic question to ask in a democracy. (Applause)"},{"time":103467,"text":"It wasn't like I was asking for the code to a nuclear bunker,"},{"time":106374,"text":"or anything like that, but the amount of resistance I got"},{"time":109227,"text":"from this Freedom of Information request,"},{"time":111750,"text":"you would have thought I'd asked something like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114994,"text":"So I fought for about five years doing this,"},{"time":119219,"text":"and it was one of many hundreds of requests that I made,"},{"time":122691,"text":"not -- I didn't -- Hey, look, I didn't set out, honestly,"},{"time":125644,"text":"to revolutionize the British Parliament."},{"time":127293,"text":"That was not my intention. I was just making these requests"},{"time":130724,"text":"as part of research for my first book."},{"time":133875,"text":"But it ended up in this very long, protracted legal battle"},{"time":136740,"text":"and there I was after five years fighting against Parliament"},{"time":141115,"text":"in front of three of Britain's most eminent High Court judges"},{"time":144155,"text":"waiting for their ruling about whether or not Parliament had to release this data."},{"time":148307,"text":"And I've got to tell you, I wasn't that hopeful,"},{"time":150415,"text":"because I'd seen the establishment. I thought,"},{"time":153140,"text":"it always sticks together. I am out of luck."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156496,"text":"Well, guess what? I won. Hooray. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":161082,"text":"Well, that's not exactly the story, because the problem was"},{"time":164505,"text":"that Parliament delayed and delayed releasing that data,"},{"time":167859,"text":"and then they tried to retrospectively change the law"},{"time":171019,"text":"so that it would no longer apply to them."},{"time":173692,"text":"The transparency law they'd passed earlier that applied to everybody else,"},{"time":176614,"text":"they tried to keep it so it didn't apply to them."},{"time":179410,"text":"What they hadn't counted on was digitization,"},{"time":182905,"text":"because that meant that all those paper receipts"},{"time":185291,"text":"had been scanned in electronically, and it was very easy"},{"time":188531,"text":"for somebody to just copy that entire database,"},{"time":191730,"text":"put it on a disk, and then just saunter outside of Parliament,"},{"time":195664,"text":"which they did, and then they shopped that disk"},{"time":198149,"text":"to the highest bidder, which was the Daily Telegraph,"},{"time":201107,"text":"and then, you all remember, there was weeks and weeks"},{"time":204314,"text":"of revelations, everything from porn movies"},{"time":207339,"text":"and bath plugs and new kitchens"},{"time":210495,"text":"and mortgages that had never been paid off."},{"time":213956,"text":"The end result was six ministers resigned,"},{"time":218643,"text":"the first speaker of the house in 300 years was forced to resign,"},{"time":222694,"text":"a new government was elected on a mandate of transparency,"},{"time":226713,"text":"120 MPs stepped down at that election,"},{"time":230496,"text":"and so far, four MPs and two lords"},{"time":234987,"text":"have done jail time for fraud."},{"time":238017,"text":"So, thank you. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":244395,"text":"Well, I tell you that story because it wasn't unique to Britain."},{"time":248670,"text":"It was an example of a culture clash that's happening"},{"time":252011,"text":"all over the world between bewigged and bestockinged"},{"time":255331,"text":"officials who think that they can rule over us"},{"time":259435,"text":"without very much prying from the public,"},{"time":261343,"text":"and then suddenly confronted with a public"},{"time":263796,"text":"who is no longer content with that arrangement,"},{"time":267234,"text":"and not only not content with it, now, more often,"},{"time":270472,"text":"armed with official data itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274846,"text":"So we are moving to this democratization of information,"},{"time":279984,"text":"and I've been in this field for quite a while."},{"time":282631,"text":"Slightly embarrassing admission: Even when I was a kid,"},{"time":285272,"text":"I used to have these little spy books, and I would, like,"},{"time":287207,"text":"see what everybody was doing in my neighborhood and log it down."},{"time":289833,"text":"I think that was a pretty good indication"},{"time":292039,"text":"about my future career as an investigative journalist,"},{"time":295120,"text":"and what I've seen from being in this access to information field for so long"},{"time":299640,"text":"is that it used to be quite a niche interest,"},{"time":302416,"text":"and it's gone mainstream. Everybody, increasingly, around the world,"},{"time":305567,"text":"wants to know about what people in power are doing."},{"time":308735,"text":"They want a say in decisions that are made in their name"},{"time":312143,"text":"and with their money. It's this democratization of information"},{"time":315166,"text":"that I think is an information enlightenment,"},{"time":317872,"text":"and it has many of the same principles of the first Enlightenment."},{"time":321335,"text":"It's about searching for the truth,"},{"time":324330,"text":"not because somebody says it's true, \"because I say so.\""},{"time":328527,"text":"No, it's about trying to find the truth based on"},{"time":331001,"text":"what you can see and what can be tested."},{"time":333630,"text":"That, in the first Enlightenment, led to questions about"},{"time":336298,"text":"the right of kings, the divine right of kings to rule over people,"},{"time":339807,"text":"or that women should be subordinate to men,"},{"time":341984,"text":"or that the Church was the official word of God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344687,"text":"Obviously the Church weren't very happy about this,"},{"time":347123,"text":"and they tried to suppress it,"},{"time":349224,"text":"but what they hadn't counted on was technology,"},{"time":352295,"text":"and then they had the printing press, which suddenly"},{"time":354720,"text":"enabled these ideas to spread cheaply, far and fast,"},{"time":358112,"text":"and people would come together in coffee houses,"},{"time":360952,"text":"discuss the ideas, plot revolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363768,"text":"In our day, we have digitization. That strips all the physical mass out of information,"},{"time":368359,"text":"so now it's almost zero cost to copy and share information."},{"time":371764,"text":"Our printing press is the Internet. Our coffee houses are social networks."},{"time":376001,"text":"We're moving to what I would think of as a fully connected system,"},{"time":381103,"text":"and we have global decisions to make in this system,"},{"time":383976,"text":"decisions about climate, about finance systems,"},{"time":387662,"text":"about resources. And think about it --"},{"time":391003,"text":"if we want to make an important decision about buying a house,"},{"time":393465,"text":"we don't just go off. I mean, I don't know about you,"},{"time":395979,"text":"but I want to see a lot of houses before I put that much money into it."},{"time":399323,"text":"And if we're thinking about a finance system,"},{"time":401678,"text":"we need a lot of information to take in. It's just not possible"},{"time":405322,"text":"for one person to take in the amount, the volume"},{"time":409283,"text":"of information, and analyze it to make good decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413049,"text":"So that's why we're seeing increasingly this demand"},{"time":416075,"text":"for access to information."},{"time":418460,"text":"That's why we're starting to see more disclosure laws"},{"time":420769,"text":"come out, so for example, on the environment,"},{"time":422745,"text":"there's the Aarhus Convention,"},{"time":424461,"text":"which is a European directive that gives people"},{"time":426489,"text":"a very strong right to know, so if your water company"},{"time":429237,"text":"is dumping water into your river, sewage water"},{"time":432607,"text":"into your river, you have a right to know about it."},{"time":435655,"text":"In the finance industry, you now have more of a right"},{"time":439534,"text":"to know about what's going on, so we have"},{"time":442087,"text":"different anti-bribery laws, money regulations,"},{"time":445040,"text":"increased corporate disclosure, so you can now track assets across borders."},{"time":449113,"text":"And it's getting harder to hide assets, tax avoidance,"},{"time":454357,"text":"pay inequality. So that's great. We're starting to find out"},{"time":457492,"text":"more and more about these systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460211,"text":"And they're all moving to this central system,"},{"time":463003,"text":"this fully connected system,"},{"time":465370,"text":"all of them except one. Can you guess which one?"},{"time":468577,"text":"It's the system which underpins all these other systems."},{"time":471248,"text":"It's the system by which we organize and exercise power,"},{"time":475406,"text":"and there I'm talking about politics, because in politics,"},{"time":478336,"text":"we're back to this system, this top-down hierarchy."},{"time":482463,"text":"And how is it possible that the volume of information"},{"time":485544,"text":"can be processed that needs to in this system?"},{"time":488355,"text":"Well, it just can't. That's it."},{"time":490971,"text":"And I think this is largely what's behind the crisis"},{"time":493678,"text":"of legitimacy in our different governments right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498001,"text":"So I've told you a bit about what I did"},{"time":500184,"text":"to try and drag Parliament, kicking and screaming,"},{"time":502869,"text":"into the 21st century, and I'm just going to give you"},{"time":505384,"text":"a couple of examples of what a few other people I know"},{"time":508048,"text":"are doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509268,"text":"So this is a guy called Seb Bacon. He's a computer"},{"time":512487,"text":"programmer, and he built a site called Alaveteli,"},{"time":516445,"text":"and what it is, it's a Freedom of Information platform."},{"time":521215,"text":"It's open-source, with documentation, and it allows you"},{"time":524190,"text":"to make a Freedom of Information request,"},{"time":527293,"text":"to ask your public body a question, so"},{"time":530262,"text":"it takes all the hassle out of it, and I can tell you"},{"time":533382,"text":"that there is a lot of hassle making these requests,"},{"time":535470,"text":"so it takes all of that hassle out, and you just type in your question,"},{"time":539014,"text":"for example, how many police officers have a criminal record?"},{"time":543485,"text":"It zooms it off to the appropriate person, it tells you"},{"time":547326,"text":"when the time limit is coming to an end, it keeps track of all"},{"time":550814,"text":"the correspondence, it posts it up there,"},{"time":552466,"text":"and it becomes an archive of public knowledge."},{"time":556121,"text":"So that's open-source and it can be used in any country"},{"time":559694,"text":"where there is some kind of Freedom of Information law."},{"time":562605,"text":"So there's a list there of the different countries that have it,"},{"time":565815,"text":"and then there's a few more coming on board."},{"time":567610,"text":"So if any of you out there like the sound of that"},{"time":570170,"text":"and have a law like that in your country,"},{"time":572903,"text":"I know that Seb would love to hear from you"},{"time":574942,"text":"about collaborating and getting that into your country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579014,"text":"This is Birgitta Jónsdóttir. She's an Icelandic MP."},{"time":583309,"text":"And quite an unusual MP. In Iceland, she was"},{"time":587143,"text":"one of the protesters who was outside of Parliament"},{"time":590460,"text":"when the country's economy collapsed,"},{"time":594206,"text":"and then she was elected on a reform mandate,"},{"time":598100,"text":"and she's now spearheading this project."},{"time":600467,"text":"It's the Icelandic Modern Media Initiative,"},{"time":603354,"text":"and they've just got funding to make it an international"},{"time":605619,"text":"modern media project, and this is taking all of the best laws"},{"time":609058,"text":"around the world about freedom of expression,"},{"time":611994,"text":"protection of whistleblowers, protection from libel,"},{"time":614789,"text":"source protection, and trying to make Iceland a publishing haven."},{"time":619263,"text":"It's a place where your data can be free, so when we think"},{"time":621684,"text":"about, increasingly, how governments want to access user data,"},{"time":625099,"text":"what they're trying to do in Iceland is make this safe haven"},{"time":627871,"text":"where it can happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630608,"text":"In my own field of investigative journalism, we're also"},{"time":633746,"text":"having to start thinking globally, so this is a site called"},{"time":636576,"text":"Investigative Dashboard. And if you're trying to track"},{"time":639699,"text":"a dictator's assets, for example, Hosni Mubarak,"},{"time":642682,"text":"you know, he's just funneling out cash from his country"},{"time":646127,"text":"when he knows he's in trouble, and what you want to do"},{"time":648666,"text":"to investigate that is, you need to have access to"},{"time":651062,"text":"all of the world's, as many as you can,"},{"time":653361,"text":"companies' house registrations databases."},{"time":656144,"text":"So this is a website that tries to agglomerate all of those"},{"time":660582,"text":"databases into one place so you can start searching for,"},{"time":663837,"text":"you know, his relatives, his friends, the head of his security services."},{"time":667505,"text":"You can try and find out how he's moving out assets"},{"time":670256,"text":"from that country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672982,"text":"But again, when it comes to the decisions which are"},{"time":676615,"text":"impacting us the most, perhaps, the most important"},{"time":679615,"text":"decisions that are being made about war and so forth,"},{"time":682904,"text":"again we can't just make a Freedom of Information request."},{"time":685833,"text":"It's really difficult. So we're still having to rely on"},{"time":688941,"text":"illegitimate ways of getting information, through leaks."},{"time":693023,"text":"So when the Guardian did this investigation about"},{"time":696065,"text":"the Afghan War, you know, they can't walk into"},{"time":699215,"text":"the Department of Defense and ask for all the information."},{"time":702679,"text":"You know, they're just not going to get it."},{"time":704621,"text":"So this came from leaks of tens of thousands of dispatches"},{"time":708161,"text":"that were written by American soldiers"},{"time":710567,"text":"about the Afghan War, and leaked,"},{"time":713126,"text":"and then they're able to do this investigation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716777,"text":"Another rather large investigation is around world diplomacy."},{"time":722345,"text":"Again, this is all based around leaks,"},{"time":724845,"text":"251,000 U.S. diplomatic cables, and I was involved"},{"time":730096,"text":"in this investigation because I got this leak"},{"time":734037,"text":"through a leak from a disgruntled WikiLeaker"},{"time":737406,"text":"and ended up going to work at the Guardian."},{"time":740175,"text":"So I can tell you firsthand what it was like to have access"},{"time":742599,"text":"to this leak. It was amazing. I mean, it was amazing."},{"time":744566,"text":"It reminded me of that scene in \"The Wizard of Oz.\""},{"time":748216,"text":"Do you know the one I mean? Where the little dog Toto"},{"time":750704,"text":"runs across to where the wizard [is], and he pulls back,"},{"time":753555,"text":"the dog's pulling back the curtain, and --"},{"time":755017,"text":"\"Don't look behind the screen. Don't look at the man behind the screen.\""},{"time":759000,"text":"It was just like that, because what you started to see"},{"time":761136,"text":"is that all of these grand statesmen, these very pompous"},{"time":764087,"text":"politicians, they were just like us."},{"time":767185,"text":"They all bitched about each other. I mean, quite gossipy,"},{"time":769745,"text":"those cables. Okay, but I thought it was a very important"},{"time":772416,"text":"point for all of us to grasp, these are human beings"},{"time":775017,"text":"just like us. They don't have special powers."},{"time":776968,"text":"They're not magic. They are not our parents."},{"time":780791,"text":"Beyond that, what I found most fascinating"},{"time":785640,"text":"was the level of endemic corruption that I saw"},{"time":788264,"text":"across all different countries, and particularly centered"},{"time":791419,"text":"around the heart of power, around public officials"},{"time":794247,"text":"who were embezzling the public's money"},{"time":796863,"text":"for their own personal enrichment, and allowed to do that"},{"time":799881,"text":"because of official secrecy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803264,"text":"So I've mentioned WikiLeaks, because surely what could be"},{"time":806891,"text":"more open than publishing all the material?"},{"time":809722,"text":"Because that is what Julian Assange did."},{"time":812793,"text":"He wasn't content with the way the newspapers published it"},{"time":815361,"text":"to be safe and legal. He threw it all out there."},{"time":819158,"text":"That did end up with vulnerable people in Afghanistan"},{"time":822873,"text":"being exposed. It also meant that the Belarussian dictator"},{"time":826289,"text":"was given a handy list of all the pro-democracy campaigners"},{"time":830059,"text":"in that country who had spoken to the U.S. government."},{"time":833545,"text":"Is that radical openness? I say it's not, because for me,"},{"time":838017,"text":"what it means, it doesn't mean abdicating power,"},{"time":841519,"text":"responsibility, accountability, it's actually being a partner"},{"time":845273,"text":"with power. It's about sharing responsibility,"},{"time":848289,"text":"sharing accountability. Also, the fact that"},{"time":851201,"text":"he threatened to sue me because I got a leak of his leaks,"},{"time":853338,"text":"I thought that showed a remarkable sort of inconsistency"},{"time":856023,"text":"in ideology, to be honest, as well. (Laughs)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":861864,"text":"The other thing is that power is incredibly seductive,"},{"time":865198,"text":"and you must have two real qualities, I think,"},{"time":867866,"text":"when you come to the table, when you're dealing"},{"time":870279,"text":"with power, talking about power,"},{"time":872013,"text":"because of its seductive capacity."},{"time":874386,"text":"You've got to have skepticism and humility."},{"time":877405,"text":"Skepticism, because you must always be challenging."},{"time":879998,"text":"I want to see why do you -- you just say so? That's not good enough."},{"time":883030,"text":"I want to see the evidence behind why that's so."},{"time":885745,"text":"And humility because we are all human. We all make mistakes."},{"time":890238,"text":"And if you don't have skepticism and humility,"},{"time":893030,"text":"then it's a really short journey to go from reformer"},{"time":896125,"text":"to autocrat, and I think you only have to read \"Animal Farm\""},{"time":900734,"text":"to get that message about how power corrupts people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":906677,"text":"So what is the solution? It is, I believe, to embody"},{"time":912145,"text":"within the rule of law rights to information."},{"time":915612,"text":"At the moment our rights are incredibly weak."},{"time":918247,"text":"In a lot of countries, we have Official Secrets Acts,"},{"time":921229,"text":"including in Britain here. We have an Official Secrets Act"},{"time":923392,"text":"with no public interest test. So that means it's a crime,"},{"time":926508,"text":"people are punished, quite severely in a lot of cases,"},{"time":930674,"text":"for publishing or giving away official information."},{"time":934877,"text":"Now wouldn't it be amazing, and really, this is what I want"},{"time":938355,"text":"all of you to think about, if we had an Official Disclosure Act"},{"time":941917,"text":"where officials were punished if they were found"},{"time":945293,"text":"to have suppressed or hidden information"},{"time":948253,"text":"that was in the public interest?"},{"time":950438,"text":"So that -- yes. Yes! My power pose. (Applause) (Laughs)"},{"time":957338,"text":"I would like us to work towards that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959883,"text":"So it's not all bad news. I mean, there definitely is"},{"time":963803,"text":"progress on the line, but I think what we find is that"},{"time":966758,"text":"the closer that we get right into the heart of power,"},{"time":969934,"text":"the more opaque, closed it becomes."},{"time":974358,"text":"So it was only just the other week that I heard London's"},{"time":977438,"text":"Metropolitan Police Commissioner talking about why"},{"time":980935,"text":"the police need access to all of our communications,"},{"time":985527,"text":"spying on us without any judicial oversight,"},{"time":988590,"text":"and he said it was a matter of life and death."},{"time":990256,"text":"He actually said that, it was a matter of life and death."},{"time":993503,"text":"There was no evidence. He presented no evidence of that."},{"time":997725,"text":"It was just, \"Because I say so."},{"time":1000847,"text":"You have to trust me. Take it on faith.\""},{"time":1004095,"text":"Well, I'm sorry, people, but we are back"},{"time":1006094,"text":"to the pre-Enlightenment Church,"},{"time":1009799,"text":"and we need to fight against that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1013575,"text":"So he was talking about the law in Britain which is"},{"time":1016863,"text":"the Communications Data Bill, an absolutely outrageous piece of legislation."},{"time":1021089,"text":"In America, you have the Cyber Intelligence Sharing and Protection Act."},{"time":1024695,"text":"You've got drones now being considered for domestic surveillance."},{"time":1028335,"text":"You have the National Security Agency building"},{"time":1031095,"text":"the world's giantest spy center. It's just this colossal --"},{"time":1034623,"text":"it's five times bigger than the U.S. Capitol,"},{"time":1037095,"text":"in which they're going to intercept and analyze"},{"time":1038897,"text":"communications, traffic and personal data"},{"time":1041846,"text":"to try and figure out who's the troublemaker in society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1045159,"text":"Well, to go back to our original story, the parents"},{"time":1049959,"text":"have panicked. They've locked all the doors."},{"time":1053809,"text":"They've kitted out the house with CCTV cameras."},{"time":1056895,"text":"They're watching all of us. They've dug a basement,"},{"time":1059647,"text":"and they've built a spy center to try and run algorithms"},{"time":1062311,"text":"and figure out which ones of us are troublesome,"},{"time":1064983,"text":"and if any of us complain about that, we're arrested for terrorism."},{"time":1069217,"text":"Well, is that a fairy tale or a living nightmare?"},{"time":1072791,"text":"Some fairy tales have happy endings. Some don't."},{"time":1076450,"text":"I think we've all read the Grimms' fairy tales, which are,"},{"time":1079197,"text":"indeed, very grim."},{"time":1081695,"text":"But the world isn't a fairy tale, and it could be more brutal"},{"time":1086917,"text":"than we want to acknowledge."},{"time":1089721,"text":"Equally, it could be better than we've been led to believe,"},{"time":1092010,"text":"but either way, we have to start seeing it exactly as it is,"},{"time":1095721,"text":"with all of its problems, because it's only by seeing it"},{"time":1099570,"text":"with all of its problems that we'll be able to fix them"},{"time":1102063,"text":"and live in a world in which we can all be"},{"time":1106134,"text":"happily ever after. (Laughs) Thank you very much."},{"time":1109820,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1113055,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}